This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Fix a bug where `autoPaths: true` with empty `customPaths` doesn't work for series URLs
   - Fix Chinese (Unicode) post URLs broken under autoPaths/customPaths routes
   - Fix test failures caused by `site.config.ts` having `autoPaths: true` and a renamed test fixture file
   - Fix integration test failures caused by the same renamed fixture
   - Address CodeRabbit PR #46 review comments:
     - Round 1: align `reservedSlugs` hardcoded list with `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` constant
     - Round 2: replace `in` operator with `Object.hasOwn()` for prototype-safe checks, and add missing test coverage for autoPaths routing scenarios

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Next.js 15+ App Router with `output: "export"` (static export), `dynamicParams = false`
   - `generateStaticParams()` must return non-empty params for all dynamic routes
   - ESM live bindings and how `mock.module()` in bun:test updates them
   - `autoPaths` feature: when enabled, series posts served at `/{series-slug}/{post-slug}` instead of `/posts/{slug}`
   - `customPaths` feature: per-series custom URL prefix overriding `autoPaths`
   - Percent-encoding workaround for Unicode slugs in Next.js dev mode under `output: "export"` (dev server sends encoded URLs, but `generateStaticParams` provides raw Unicode)
   - `in` operator vs `Object.hasOwn()` for own-property checks (prototype chain safety)
   - bun:test module mocking: `mock.module()` replaces in place, but live binding updates may not reliably propagate to previously-cached modules in certain conditions
   - Test isolation: `beforeAll`/`afterAll` vs `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for mock state management

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`src/lib/urls.ts`**
     - Changed `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` from `const` to `export const`, added `'posts'` and `'search'`
     - Changed `if (slug in customPaths)` → `if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug))`
     ```typescript
     export const RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS = new Set([
       'posts', 'series', 'books', 'flows', 'tags', 'authors', 'archive', 'notes', 'graph', 'search', 'page', 'api',
     ]);
     // in validateSeriesAutoPaths:
     if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug)) continue; // Has an explicit override — skip
     ```

   - **`src/app/[slug]/page.tsx`**
     - Added `getAllSeries`, `getSeriesAutoPaths`, `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` to imports
     - `generateStaticParams`: added autoPaths series slug generation, replaced hardcoded reserved list with `...RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS`
     - `generateMetadata` and `Page`: extended `matchedSeriesSlug` to also detect autoPaths series
     - Changed `in customPaths` → `Object.hasOwn(customPaths, ...)` in 3 places
     ```typescript
     const matchedSeriesSlug =
       Object.entries(customPaths).find(([, path]) => path === slug)?.[0] ??
       (getSeriesAutoPaths() && !Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug) && getSeriesData(slug) ? slug : undefined);
     // generateStaticParams reservedSlugs:
     const reservedSlugs = new Set([
       ...pages.map(p => p.slug),
       basePath,
       ...Object.values(customPaths),
       ...autoPathSlugs,
       ...RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS,
     ]);
     ```

   - **`src/app/[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx`**
     - Added Unicode encoding workaround for `generateStaticParams` (mirrors `posts/[slug]/page.tsx`)
     - Changed `in customPaths` → `Object.hasOwn(customPaths, ...)` in 2 places
     ```typescript
     // Work around Next dev static-param checks for percent-encoded Unicode postSlugs
     if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {
       const existing = new Set(params.map(p => `${p.slug}/${p.postSlug}`));
       for (const p of [...params]) {
         const encodedPostSlug = encodeURIComponent(p.postSlug);
         const key = `${p.slug}/${encodedPostSlug}`;
         if (!existing.has(key)) {
           existing.add(key);
           params.push({ slug: p.slug, postSlug: encodedPostSlug });
         }
